.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "APRIL 23 2024" "Simple Shell Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A custom UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a command language interpreter that executes commands read from the standard input or from a file. It mimics the basic behavior of the sh (Bourne Shell).

The shell works by:
1. Displaying a prompt and waiting for the user to type a command.
2. Parsing the input into tokens (arguments).
3. Checking if the command is a builtin.
4. Locating the command in the PATH if it's not a builtin or a direct path.
5. Executing the command in a new process using fork and execve.
6. Waiting for the command to finish and returning to the prompt.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Interactive Mode
The shell displays a prompt "$ " when connected to a terminal (isatty).
.TP
.B Non-Interactive Mode
The shell can read commands via pipes or redirected files: 'echo "ls" | ./hsh'.
.TP
.B PATH Handling
The shell automatically searches for executables in the directories listed in the PATH environment variable.
.TP
.B Command Line Arguments
Supports commands with multiple arguments (e.g., 'ls -l /tmp').

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Terminates the shell and exits with the current shell status.
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.B simple_shell
returns the status of the last command executed. If a command is not found, it returns 127.

.SH EXAMPLES
.I To start the shell:
.br
    ./hsh
.br
.I To run a command with arguments:
.br
    $ /bin/ls -l
.br
    $ ls -l
.br
.I To exit:
.br
    $ exit

